[It seems the farmers are offering to create several areas that are
essentially a segregated "badger town" where cattle are prohibited. With
this allow TB and the badgers to be contained, thereby decreasing the
cattle TB or will it have no effect on the TB cases except to frustrate the
farmer because of less usable land. Only time will tell. - Mod.TG
